author: wtogami
msg: URI_SKIPPED_* detects attempts of known good URI flooding, which seems to be targeted at defeating URIBL filtering of some other filter software.
This is fairly common in my own corpus, but I don't know how widespread it is.  Masschecks should tell us if this is worthwhile to keep.
